Notes:
- Marker template said "Files: wg-engine.js, hunt-render.js" but the brief
  itself instructed the rAF tick caller (wg-game.js) to gate on isHitPaused()
  so runtime.elapsed wouldn't advance during the pause window. Touched
  wg-game.js minimally — added "&& !WG.Engine.isHitPaused()" to the
  existing _tutorialPaused guard. Not on the do-not-touch list.
- Hit-flash on enemies overlays an additive-white ellipse over the body
  silhouette for 80ms (alpha decay from 0.6 to 0). c._lastDamageAt is set
  via subscription to enemy:damaged from hunt-render init() — no edit
  required to hunt-enemies.js.
- Player squash-and-stretch on player:swing wraps drawAnimeGirl in a
  ctx.scale transform: 1.08x / 0.92y at t=0, eased back to 1.0 over 60ms.
- Trauma transform wraps WORLD render only (between WG.Render.clear and
  the existing ctx.scale(ZOOM,ZOOM)) so HUD + edge-pulse stay screen-anchored.
- drawStump foliage flashBoost factor bumped 30→48 per "slightly increase
  the flash intensity" hint in the brief. drawStump's existing wobble +
  hit-flash was kept as-is otherwise.
- Concurrent workers (W-FX-NumbersAndPulse Concern B HUD-pulse, and
  W-FX-Particles-And-Magnet adding js/hunt/hunt-fx.js + 3 hookup lines)
  had uncommitted work in the same hunt-render.js. Stashed/popped around
  my commits to avoid clobbering; their work is preserved in the working
  tree (uncommitted, theirs to commit).
- Verified live in wraithgrove preview server (port 3996): WG.HuntRender.addTrauma,
  WG.Engine.hitPause, WG.Engine.isHitPaused all defined; calling
  hitPause(120) immediately reports isHitPaused()===true. No console
